---
import ServiceLayout from '../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';

const schemaData = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "name": "Marketing Agency for Gyms & Fitness Centres Singapore",
    "description": "Full-service marketing agency for gyms and fitness centres in Singapore. SEO, Google Ads, social, branding, websites — built for membership growth. From S$3,000/month.",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Jraft Creative",
      "url": "https://jraftcreative.com/",
      "logo": "https://jraftcreative.com/images/logo.png",
      "telephone": "+6582234578",
      "address": {
        "@type": "PostalAddress",
        "streetAddress": "60 Paya Lebar Road, Paya Lebar Square",
        "postalCode": "409051",
        "addressLocality": "Singapore",
        "addressCountry": "SG"
      }
    },
    "areaServed": { "@type": "Country", "name": "Singapore" },
    "serviceType": "Gym & Fitness Centre Digital Marketing",
    "offers": [
      { "@type": "Offer", "name": "Essential Gym Marketing", "price": "3000", "priceCurrency": "SGD", "description": "Single-channel focus (SEO or Social), Google Business Profile optimisation, monthly content, and reporting for single-location gyms and boutique studios" },
      { "@type": "Offer", "name": "Growth Gym Marketing", "price": "5500", "priceCurrency": "SGD", "description": "Multi-channel: SEO + Google Ads + IG/TikTok, trial-funnel content production, GCLID lead tracking, bi-weekly reporting for established gyms scaling memberships" },
      { "@type": "Offer", "name": "Enterprise Gym Marketing", "price": "10000", "priceCurrency": "SGD", "description": "Full-service across all channels, dedicated strategist, video production for class and transformation Reels, brand refresh, and weekly reporting for multi-location fitness chains" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How much does marketing cost for a gym in Singapore?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Gym marketing in Singapore starts at S$3,000 per month for essential single-channel work (typically SEO or social media). Growth packages at S$5,500/month combine SEO, Google Ads, and IG/TikTok with trial-funnel tracking. Enterprise packages at S$10,000+/month add video production, brand refresh, and a dedicated strategist for multi-location chains. Single-location boutique gyms typically start at Essential; established gyms scaling memberships across catchments need the Growth tier minimum." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why can't I just rely on ClassPass and Google Business Profile for members?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ClassPass sends high-volume but low-margin visits — gym-hoppers comparing five studios in a single week, with the platform taking a cut on every session. Google Business Profile alone captures only the bottom-of-funnel 'gym near me' searches. Direct-to-gym marketing (SEO, Google Ads, IG, TikTok) builds a brand that potential members search for by name, drives full-fee memberships, and captures the inspiration and trial stages before the comparison happens." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What's the buyer journey for joining a gym in Singapore?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Singapore gym buyers move through five stages: Awareness (IG Reels, TikTok transformations, Google searches for 'gym near me') → Trial (free session, 7-day pass, or first-class promo) → Sign-up (membership conversion at front desk or via WhatsApp) → Retention (first 90 days are make-or-break) → Referral (member-led word of mouth). Most gyms only market to Awareness and never build retention or referral systems — which is where the long-term margin lives." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Which marketing channels work best for gyms in Singapore?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Six channels in priority order for most gyms: (1) SEO for catchment searches ('gym near me', 'personal training Tampines'), (2) Google Ads for high-intent terms during January and post-summer sign-up peaks, (3) Instagram Reels for facility tours and class previews, (4) TikTok for member transformations and trainer technique content, (5) branding so you're not competing on price alone, (6) a website that converts visits into trial bookings. We build cross-channel plans based on your gym's format and budget." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How long before marketing brings new gym memberships?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Google Ads can generate trial-visit bookings within the first 7-14 days once tracking is set up. Social media content compounds over 8-12 weeks. SEO and GEO typically show ranking and AI-citation improvements within 3-6 months for catchment-area keywords. Most gym clients see a meaningful increase in trial visits and membership sign-ups within the first 60 days of a full-service campaign — provided the operator replies to WhatsApp and DM enquiries fast enough to close them." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do you work with boutique gyms as well as large fitness chains?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. We work with boutique strength studios, CrossFit boxes, 24-hour commercial gyms, personal training studios, condo gym operators, and multi-location fitness chains. Each format has its own competitive positioning, pricing model, and target audience. Boutique studios typically run Essential or Growth; multi-location chains need Enterprise for per-catchment campaign management. We tailor every plan to your gym's format and growth stage." } }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://jraftcreative.com/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Marketing Agency for Gyms & Fitness Centres Singapore", "item": "https://jraftcreative.com/gym-marketing-singapore/" }
    ]
  }
];
---

<style is:global>
  /* Hide the global background grid pattern on this page only */
  .animated-bg__grid { display: none; }

  /* More-prominent related-service pills — match challenge-card-v2 green treatment */
  #related-services .related-service-link {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.14) 0%, rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.06) 100%), rgba(20, 28, 32, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.35);
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.25s ease, border-color 0.25s ease, background 0.25s ease, box-shadow 0.25s ease;
  }
  #related-services .related-service-link:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.22) 0%, rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.1) 100%), rgba(20, 28, 32, 0.7);
    border-color: rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.6);
    color: var(--accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px -8px rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.3);
  }

  /* Separate the CTA section from related-services with bg-alt */
  .service-cta-section {
    background: var(--bg-alt) !important;
  }

  /* Gym Member Funnel — 5-stage horizontal flow with green accents */
  .renovation-funnel {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 56px 0 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 48px;
    counter-reset: funnel;
  }
  .funnel-stage {
    position: relative;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 28px 20px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.14) 0%, rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.06) 100%), rgba(20, 28, 32, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.28);
    border-radius: 12px;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
  }
  .funnel-stage:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.55);
    box-shadow: 0 16px 40px -16px rgba(73, 184, 137, 0.3);
  }
  .funnel-stage h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .funnel-stage p {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .funnel-stage:not(:last-child)::after {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    right: -34px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    z-index: 2;
    line-height: 1;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .renovation-funnel {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 32px;
    }
    .funnel-stage:nth-child(2n)::after,
    .funnel-stage:last-child::after {
      display: none;
    }
    .funnel-stage:nth-child(2n-1)::after {
      right: -22px;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .renovation-funnel {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 20px;
    }
    .funnel-stage::after {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>

<ServiceLayout
  title="Marketing Agency for Gyms & Fitness Centres Singapore | Jraft Creative"
  description="Full-service marketing agency for gyms and fitness centres in Singapore. SEO, Google Ads, social, branding, websites — built for membership growth. From $3,000/mo."
  canonical="https://jraftcreative.com/gym-marketing-singapore/"
  ogTitle="Marketing Agency for Gyms & Fitness Centres Singapore | Jraft Creative"
  ogDescription="Full-service marketing agency for gyms and fitness centres in Singapore. SEO, Google Ads, social, branding, websites — built for membership growth. From $3,000 SGD/month."
  ogImage="https://jraftcreative.com/images/og-webdev.jpg"
  keywords="gym marketing singapore, fitness centre marketing agency, gym digital marketing singapore, marketing for gyms singapore, personal training marketing, Jraft Creative"
  schemaData={schemaData}
  heroLabel="Marketing for Gyms & Fitness Centres"
  heroTitle='Marketing Agency for <span class="highlight">Gyms &amp; Fitness Centres in Singapore</span>'
  heroSubtitle="Most prospective members in Singapore compare three to five gyms online before booking a trial — and most gyms are invisible during that window. We build full-service marketing strategies (SEO, GEO, Google Ads, IG/TikTok, branding, websites) designed for how Singapore members actually choose where to train."
  heroImage="/images/service-gym.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Modern Singapore gym interior — gym and fitness centre marketing"
  heroButtons={[
    { text: "Get a Free Quote", href: "/contact/", class: "btn btn-primary" },
    { text: "Chat on WhatsApp", href: "https://wa.me/6582234578?text=Hi%20Jraft%20Creative%2C%20I%20run%20a%20gym%20in%20Singapore%20and%20need%20marketing%20help.", class: "btn btn-secondary" }
  ]}
  whatsappText="Hi Jraft Creative, I run a gym in Singapore and need marketing help."
  ctaLabel="Ready to Get Started?"
  ctaTitle='Let Us <span class="highlight">Grow</span> Your <span class="highlight">Membership Pipeline</span>'
  ctaDescription="Book a free consultation and tell us about your gym — your format, your catchment, your current marketing. We'll get back to you within 24 hours with a tailored, channel-by-channel marketing plan."
  ctaButtons={[
    { text: "Get a Free Quote", href: "/contact/", class: "btn btn-primary" },
    { text: "Chat on WhatsApp", href: "https://wa.me/6582234578?text=Hi%20Jraft%20Creative%2C%20I%20run%20a%20gym%20in%20Singapore%20and%20need%20marketing%20help.", class: "btn btn-secondary" }
  ]}
  hideDefaultCta={false}
>

  <!-- ========== THE CHALLENGE ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="challenge" aria-label="Why gyms need marketing in Singapore">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">The Challenge</p>
        <h2>The <span class="highlight">Best</span> Gyms Are Still <span class="highlight">Losing Members</span> to Gyms with <span class="highlight">Better Marketing</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal">
        <p>By the time a prospective member walks in, they've already compared three to five gyms online. Most gyms are invisible during that window — and the studios winning full-fee memberships know exactly why.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-details-grid challenge-grid-v2" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));">
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 reveal reveal-d1">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>The Comparison Window</h3>
            <p>Prospective members search Google, Instagram, TikTok, Facebook, and AI tools before contacting a single gym. By then they've already shortlisted three to five. If you're not visible on those platforms, you're not getting the trial booking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 reveal reveal-d2">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>The ClassPass Trap</h3>
            <p>ClassPass and pay-per-session platforms own the discovery layer. Gyms relying on them get gym-hoppers comparing five studios a week, pay platform fees on every visit, and never build the brand that drives full-fee direct sign-ups.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 reveal reveal-d3">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>The Full-Fee Gap</h3>
            <p>Gyms winning premium memberships and long retention aren't the ones with the loudest ClassPass listings. They're the ones showing up directly in Google catchment searches, dominating IG Reels, and converting trials with a strong website and brand.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== WHAT WE DELIVER ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="sub-services" style="background: var(--bg-alt);" aria-label="Marketing services for gyms in Singapore">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">What We Deliver</p>
        <h2>Six <span class="highlight">Marketing Channels</span> Every Gym <span class="highlight">Needs</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal">
        <p>We build marketing strategies specifically for gyms and fitness centres — combining catchment SEO, AI search optimisation (GEO), paid search, social content, branding, and conversion-focused web design.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-details-grid deliver-grid">
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 deliver-card-with-bg reveal reveal-d1" style="background-image: url('/images/detail-local-seo.webp');">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3><a href="/gym-seo-singapore/">SEO for Gyms</a></h3>
            <p>Rank for catchment searches like "gym near me" and "personal training Tampines." Beat ClassPass and aggregator listings on the long-tail queries where members are ready to book a trial visit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 deliver-card-with-bg reveal reveal-d2" style="background-image: url('/images/detail-ai.webp');">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3><a href="/geo-agency-singapore/">GEO (AI Search Optimisation)</a></h3>
            <p>Get cited when prospective members ask ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity, or Google AI Mode for "best gym for strength training Singapore." Same citation playbook we've used for our own agency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 deliver-card-with-bg reveal reveal-d3" style="background-image: url('/images/detail-google-ads.webp');">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3><a href="/gym-google-ads-singapore/">Google Ads for Gyms</a></h3>
            <p>High-intent campaigns timed to January and post-summer sign-up peaks. GCLID tracking from click to signed membership. Industry benchmark CPL: S$15–S$45 for trial bookings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 deliver-card-with-bg reveal reveal-d1" style="background-image: url('/images/detail-reels-video.webp');">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3><a href="/gym-social-media-singapore/">Social Media for Gyms</a></h3>
            <p>The Member Transformation Formula — 30s class-preview Reels, 60s technique TikToks, Instagram and Facebook content. Built for how Singapore members actually scroll and shortlist.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 deliver-card-with-bg reveal reveal-d2" style="background-image: url('/images/detail-graphic-design.webp');">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3><a href="/gym-branding-singapore/">Branding for Gyms</a></h3>
            <p>The brand system that lifts you out of price-only comparisons. Logo, palette, kit template, photo direction — positioned by gym format so members pick you over the cheaper option.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 deliver-card-with-bg reveal reveal-d3" style="background-image: url('/images/detail-business-website.webp');">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3><a href="/gym-website-design-singapore/">Websites for Gyms</a></h3>
            <p>The site that closes the trial. Facility-led design, class schedule, trainer profiles, transparent pricing, single-field booking form, and fast mobile performance for members comparing options.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== WHY CHOOSE US ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="why-us" aria-label="Why choose Jraft Creative for gym marketing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Why Jraft Creative</p>
        <h2><span class="highlight">Marketing</span> Built for How <span class="highlight">Gym Members</span> Actually <span class="highlight">Decide</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal">
        <p>Most marketing agencies pitching gyms are PR-led generalists. They produce nice-looking decks, send press releases nobody reads, and bill retainers without ever tracking a single signed membership back to a campaign. We are the opposite — full-service, performance-led, and built around the gym member journey rather than around press placements. We specialise in catchment-area campaigns across Tampines, Bukit Timah, Jurong, Tanjong Pagar, and other high-fitness-density Singapore neighbourhoods.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-details-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));">
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 reveal reveal-d1">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Facility & Member Storytelling</h3>
            <p>Fitness is a visual, social category. We treat your facility, classes, and member transformations as the marketing asset they are — shot lists, format-by-format reformatting, and integration into your conversion-focused website.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 reveal reveal-d2">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>One Agency, All Channels</h3>
            <p>SEO, GEO, Google Ads, IG, TikTok, Facebook, branding, websites — under one roof. No coordinating between three vendors. Every channel delivers consistent positioning, design, and measurement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card challenge-card-v2 reveal reveal-d3">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Pipeline, Not Vanity Metrics</h3>
            <p>We measure trials and memberships, not impressions. GCLID offline tracking and WhatsApp-routed enquiries prove which ad click became which trial became which signed member — the only numbers that move revenue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== GYM MEMBER FUNNEL ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="buyer-funnel" style="background: var(--bg-alt);" aria-label="The Gym Member Funnel — how Singapore members decide on a gym">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">The Member Funnel</p>
        <h2>How <span class="highlight">Singapore Members</span> Actually <span class="highlight">Decide</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
        <p>From first scroll to long-term member, every gym joiner in Singapore moves through the same five stages. We build marketing campaigns that show up at each one — from inspiration through to referral.</p>
      </div>
      <ol class="renovation-funnel reveal">
        <li class="funnel-stage">
          <h3>Awareness</h3>
          <p>IG Reels, TikTok, Google, AI tools</p>
        </li>
        <li class="funnel-stage">
          <h3>Trial</h3>
          <p>Free session or trial-week pass</p>
        </li>
        <li class="funnel-stage">
          <h3>Sign-up</h3>
          <p>Membership conversion at desk or WhatsApp</p>
        </li>
        <li class="funnel-stage">
          <h3>Retention</h3>
          <p>First 90 days, engagement campaigns</p>
        </li>
        <li class="funnel-stage">
          <h3>Referral</h3>
          <p>Member word of mouth &amp; advocacy</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== PRICING ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="pricing" aria-label="Gym marketing pricing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Gym Marketing Pricing</p>
        <h2><span class="highlight">Plans</span> for Gyms of <span class="highlight">Every Size</span></h2>
        <p>Monthly retainer plans. No lock-in contracts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-pricing">
        <div class="pricing-grid">
          <div class="pricing-card reveal reveal-d1">
            <h3>Essential</h3>
            <div class="price">$3,000 <span>SGD/mo</span></div>
            <p class="pricing-desc">For single-location boutique gyms building visibility.</p>
            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>Single-channel focus (SEO or Social)</li>
              <li>Google Business Profile optimisation</li>
              <li>Review management setup</li>
              <li>4 pieces of content/month</li>
              <li>Monthly performance report</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-secondary">Get Started</a>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-card featured reveal reveal-d2">
            <h3>Growth</h3>
            <div class="price">$5,500 <span>SGD/mo</span></div>
            <p class="pricing-desc">For established gyms scaling memberships across channels.</p>
            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>SEO + Google Ads + IG/TikTok</li>
              <li>Trial-funnel content production</li>
              <li>GCLID lead tracking setup</li>
              <li>Catchment-area landing pages</li>
              <li>Bi-weekly reporting</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-card reveal reveal-d3">
            <h3>Enterprise</h3>
            <div class="price">$10,000+ <span>SGD/mo</span></div>
            <p class="pricing-desc">For multi-location chains and premium fitness clubs.</p>
            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>Full 6-channel coverage</li>
              <li>Dedicated strategist</li>
              <li>Video production for class &amp; transformation Reels</li>
              <li>Brand refresh / kit template</li>
              <li>Weekly reporting &amp; strategy calls</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-secondary">Let's Talk</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== FAQ ========== -->
  <section class="section faq-section" id="faq" style="background: var(--bg-alt);" aria-label="Frequently asked questions about marketing for gyms in Singapore">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
        <h2><span class="highlight">Gym</span> Marketing — Questions <span class="highlight">Answered</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>How much does marketing cost for a gym in Singapore?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Gym marketing in Singapore starts at S$3,000 per month for essential single-channel work (typically SEO or social media). Growth packages at S$5,500/month combine SEO, Google Ads, and IG/TikTok with trial-funnel tracking. Enterprise packages at S$10,000+/month add video production, brand refresh, and a dedicated strategist for multi-location chains. Single-location boutique gyms typically start at Essential; established gyms scaling memberships across catchments need the Growth tier minimum.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>Why can't I just rely on ClassPass and Google Business Profile for members?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>ClassPass sends high-volume but low-margin visits — gym-hoppers comparing five studios in a single week, with the platform taking a cut on every session. Google Business Profile alone captures only the bottom-of-funnel "gym near me" searches. Direct-to-gym marketing (SEO, Google Ads, IG, TikTok) builds a brand that potential members search for by name, drives full-fee memberships, and captures the inspiration and trial stages before the comparison happens.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d3">
          <summary>What's the buyer journey for joining a gym in Singapore?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Singapore gym buyers move through five stages: Awareness (IG Reels, TikTok transformations, Google searches for "gym near me") → Trial (free session, 7-day pass, or first-class promo) → Sign-up (membership conversion at front desk or via WhatsApp) → Retention (first 90 days are make-or-break) → Referral (member-led word of mouth). Most gyms only market to Awareness and never build retention or referral systems — which is where the long-term margin lives.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>Which marketing channels work best for gyms in Singapore?</summary>
